official_title: To amend title XVIII of the Social Security Act to authorize physical therapists to evaluate and treat medicare beneficiaries without a requirement for a physician referral, and for other purposes.
short_title: Medicare Patient Access to Physical Therapists Act of 2003

summary.text: Medicare Patient Access to Physical Therapists Act of 2003 - Amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act (SSA) to authorize qualified physical therapists to provide services for Medicare beneficiaries without the requirement of a physician referral.Provides for treatment of outpatient speech-language pathology services separately from outpatient physical therapy services.
